parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and leakage of the fuel line can cause a fire hazard, especially when the leak is near the exhaust system, and can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Strong smell of gasoline
fuel leaking from the fuel line
fuel puddles under the vehicle
corrosion of the fuel line
rusted fuel lines
fuel leak near the exhaust system
fuel leak in front of the rear driver's side tire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to become difficult to control, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering light comes on
the steering wheel becomes hard to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
and there may be a clicking or grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or become difficult to control, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The dashboard lights and gauges malfunction
the vehicle stalls or loses power
and there may be a burning smell or smoke.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering shaft can cause the vehicle to become difficult to control, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: There is a rattling noise coming from the dashboard
the steering wheel feels loose or wobbly
and the vehicle may pull to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or become difficult to control, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the dashboard lights and gauges malfunction
and there may be a burning smell or smoke.
